# .claudeignore — paths Claude Code agents must not read into context.
#
# This repo is pre-P5.6 spinout, so both Site and Pipeline lanes coexist
# (see /.pattern-c.yml for the lane manifest, AGENTS.md for the agent
# charter). Agents running on auto/issue-* branches sometimes need
# Pipeline-lane context (workflow editing, runbook updates) and sometimes
# need only Site-lane context (copy edits, MDX articles). The ACTIVE
# exclusions below cover only build artefacts and obvious noise; the
# Pattern C lane discipline is enforced by AGENTS.md hard rules + the
# audit script (scripts/pattern-c-audit.sh §2), not by this file.
#
# Post-spinout, the site repo's .claudeignore (rendered by the spinout
# script per docs/mothership/03-secure-architecture.md §2.3) MUST also
# exclude every Pipeline-lane path. The reference block at the bottom
# of this file is the canonical text the spinout uses; do not delete it.

# ---- ACTIVE: build artefacts and noise ----
node_modules/
.next/
.next/cache/
dist/
out/
build/
.vercel/
coverage/
*.lock
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml
*.tsbuildinfo
tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
.git/
*.min.js
*.min.css
public/
scripts/issues/
dashboard/.next/
dashboard/node_modules/

# ---- POST-SPINOUT REFERENCE (commented; copies into <slug>-site/.claudeignore at Phase 4) ----
# The spinout script (forge-spinout-dry-run.sh + the real spinout it gates)
# uncomments the lines below when rendering the site-repo copy. Pre-spinout,
# leaving them commented preserves Pipeline-lane agents' ability to read
# operator-only context; uncommenting now would break the autopilot.
#
# # Pipeline-only paths — operator IP, never read into a Site-lane context.
# # Mirrors docs/mothership/03-secure-architecture.md §2.3 byte-for-byte.
# # Issue #212 caveat: §2.3 predates Pattern C and does not cover dashboard/,
# # docs/decks/, docs/research/, docs/migrations/, docs/n8n-workflows/,
# # docs/_deprecated/, docs/wiki/, docs/ops/, docs/AI_*.md, docs/MONITORING.md,
# # docs/N8N_SETUP.md, docs/OPERATOR_SETUP.md, docs/TEMPLATE_REBUILD_PROMPT.md,
# # AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, .pattern-c.yml, or the forge-*/bootstrap-*/recheck-*/
# # seed-* script families. A separate issue should modernise §2.3 to be
# # Pattern-C-aware before the spinout uncomments this block.
# docs/operator/
# docs/clients/
# docs/mothership/
# docs/storefront/
# n8n/
# workflows-template/
# scripts/
# .github/workflows/triage.yml
# .github/workflows/execute*.yml
# .github/workflows/plan-issues.yml
# .github/workflows/deep-research.yml
# .github/workflows/codex-review.yml
# .github/workflows/auto-merge.yml
# .github/workflows/project-sync.yml
# .github/workflows/setup-cli.yml
# .github/workflows/ai-smoke-test.yml
# .github/workflows/deploy-dashboard.yml
